
[1]terre-verte

   TERRE-VERTE, n. A species of green earth, used by painters. It is an
   indurated clay, found in the earth in large flat masses, imbedded in
   strata of other species of earth. It is of a fine regular structure,
   and of a smooth glossy surface. It is found in Cyprus, France and
   Italy.
